# Copy to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) for `wrangler dev` to read
# locally. In production, set each value via:
#
#     wrangler secret put <NAME>
#
# Secrets only — non-secret config (APP, TENANT, LOG_LEVEL,
# LOG_SAMPLE) lives in `wrangler.jsonc:vars`. The Node equivalent
# puts both in `.env` because `process.env` doesn't distinguish.
#
# The Worker's `src/server/index.ts` chooses which verifier to use
# based on which of these is set; pick one branch per environment.

# --- SHARED_SECRET (single-tenant dev) -------------------------
# Used by both the server (verifier) AND the Vite dev-auth plugin
# (which injects Authorization: Bearer <SHARED_SECRET> on /v1/*
# requests in dev). The SPA bundle never ships this value — the
# plugin runs server-side and `apply: "serve"` skips production
# builds entirely.
#
# Set to a strong random value (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`) for
# any environment reachable from the public internet.
SHARED_SECRET=

# --- Production: Cloudflare Access JWT --------------------------
# Switch `src/server/index.ts` to `cloudflareAccess({ team, audience })`
# (see the `baerly-storage/auth` JSDoc) and uncomment these.
# `team` is the slug part of `<team>.cloudflareaccess.com`;
# `audience` is the Access App's "Audience (AUD) Tag".
# CF_ACCESS_TEAM_DOMAIN=
# CF_ACCESS_AUDIENCE_TAG=
